This spontaneous report was received from a consumer (patient's mother) via RMPDC - Rocky Mountain Poison 
and Drug Center and concerns a 24 month old male patient from the United States: 017475975A.
The patient's height was not reported and weight was 38 pounds. The patient's had no medical history and past 
drug history.
The patient was treated with paracetamol (160mg/5mL) (unspecified formulation, oral route of administration, batch
number: SHBSN00, expiry date: 1-AUG-2017) 12.5 ml at unspecified frequency initiated on 12-JAN-2016 for fever 
and not feeling well (off label use, drug used for unapproved indication). Concomitant medications were not 
reported.
On 12-JAN-2016, the patient inadvertently took both his dose of the paracetamol of 5mL and his 5-year-old 
brother's dose of the paracetamol of 7.5mL. The patient took a total of 12.5mL of the paracetamol (accidentally 
administered extra dose).
Action taken with paracetamol was not reported.
The outcome of events accidentally administered extra dose, off label use and drug used for unapproved indication 
was not reported. 
This report was not serious.